│ ```                                                                                        │
│ This assertion is part of the logic for handling `SplitVectorize` state in the             │
│ vectorization tree. When a `TreeEntry` `E` is in the `SplitVectorize` state, it means its  │
│ scalar operands are not uniform; they come from different sources. In this specific case,  │
│ the operands are split between two other `TreeEntry` nodes, `OpTE1` and `OpTE2`.           │
│                                                                                            │
│ The assertion expects that the first part of the scalars in `E` (specifically, the first   │
│ `OpTE1->getVectorFactor()` scalars) should exactly match the scalars in `OpTE1`. This      │
│ ensures that the vectorizer can correctly construct the vectorized instruction by          │
│ combining the results from vectorizing `OpTE1` and `OpTE2`.                                │
│                                                                                            │
